1 (x) 86 to 95; and
2 (xi) 96 and above;
3 (b) the gender of individuals;
4 (c) any period of hospitalization of the individuals related to the conditions, diagnoses, or other
5 impacts to an individual's health that have been identified by the governor as a basis for the public health
6 emergency;
7 (d) the date of death, if applicable;
8 (e) underlying conditions, if any, that may have contributed to the hospitalization or death of the
9 individuals; and
10 (f) if not disclosed pursuant to subsection (2)(e), for individuals who have died during the time
11 period for which the department is disclosing the information required in this section, personal characteristics or
12 conditions of the individuals that may be causally connected to mortality or morbidity known to be associated
13 with the public health emergency.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
16 integral part of Title 50, chapter 1, part 2, and the provisions of Title 50, chapter 1, part 2, apply to [section 1].
